---
title: Rust Shell — REPL Sequence Diagram
---
sequenceDiagram
    actor User
    participant Repl
    participant Shell
    participant Lexer
    participant Parser
    participant Executor
    participant Builtins
    participant Jobs as Jobs (Vec of Job)
    participant OS

    Note over Shell,OS: Startup
    Shell->>OS: install SIGCHLD handler
    Shell->>Repl: new()

    loop REPL Loop
        Shell->>Shell: reap_jobs() — drain SIGCHLD flag
        Shell->>Repl: readline(prompt)
        Repl->>User: print prompt
        User-->>Repl: input line
        Repl-->>Shell: Ok(line)

        Shell->>Lexer: tokenize(line)
        Lexer-->>Shell: Vec of Token

        Shell->>Parser: parse(tokens)
        Parser-->>Shell: Pipeline

        alt single builtin (no pipe)
            Shell->>Builtins: dispatch(name, args, &mut shell)
            Builtins-->>Shell: exit_status
        else external or piped pipeline
            Shell->>Executor: execute(&mut shell, pipeline)

            Executor->>OS: pipe() × (n-1) for n commands
            OS-->>Executor: pipe fds

            loop for each Command in Pipeline
                Executor->>OS: fork()
                OS-->>Executor: child pid

                Note over Executor,OS: In child process:
                Executor->>OS: dup2(pipe_in, 0)
                Executor->>OS: dup2(pipe_out, 1)
                Executor->>OS: setpgid(0, pgid)
                Executor->>OS: execvp(argv)
            end

            Executor->>OS: close parent pipe fds
            Executor->>Jobs: push Job (pgid, processes, Running)

            alt background (&)
                Note over Executor: return immediately
                Executor-->>Shell: 0
            else foreground
                Executor->>OS: tcsetpgrp(tty, pgid)
                Executor->>OS: waitpid(-pgid, WUNTRACED)
                OS-->>Executor: status (exited / stopped / signaled)
                Executor->>OS: tcsetpgrp(tty, shell_pgid)
                Executor->>Jobs: update Job.status
                Executor-->>Shell: exit_status
            end
        end

        Shell->>Shell: store last_status
    end

    Note over OS,Shell: Async — at any time
    OS-->>Shell: SIGCHLD
    Shell->>Shell: set sigchld_pending flag
    Note over Shell: handler is async-signal-safe
    Note over Shell: actual reap happens on next REPL tick